### SpotSync API – test requests (use VS Code "REST Client" or IntelliJ HTTP client)
@base = http://localhost:8080/api/v1

### Health check
GET http://localhost:8080/

### 1. Register an admin
POST {{base}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Admin User",
  "email": "admin@spotsync.com",
  "password": "securePassword123",
  "role": "admin"
}

### 2. Register a driver
POST {{base}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@spotsync.com",
  "password": "securePassword123",
  "role": "driver"
}

### 3. Login (copy the token from the response into @token below)
POST {{base}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@spotsync.com",
  "password": "securePassword123"
}

### Set your token here after login
@token = PASTE_TOKEN_HERE

### 4. Create a zone (admin only)
POST {{base}}/zones
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Terminal 1 EV Charging",
  "type": "ev_charging",
  "total_capacity": 20,
  "price_per_hour": 5.50
}

### 5. Get all zones (public)
GET {{base}}/zones

### 6. Get one zone (public)
GET {{base}}/zones/1

### 7. Reserve a spot (authenticated)
POST {{base}}/reservations
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "zone_id": 1,
  "license_plate": "ABC-1234"
}

### 8. My reservations
GET {{base}}/reservations/my-reservations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 9. All reservations (admin only)
GET {{base}}/reservations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 10. Cancel a reservation
DELETE {{base}}/reservations/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
